===Etymology===
From {{bor|en|de|Salzburg}}, from {{m|de|Salz||[[salt]]}} + {{m|de|Burg||[[castle]], [[fort]]}}, from its former importance protecting the salt trade on the [[Salzach]], itself derived from {{m|de|Salz}} + {{m|de|Aach}}, from Proto-Germanic {{m|gem-pro|*ahwō||[[water]]s, [[river]]}}.

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# {{place|en|city|in western|c/Austria}}, [[fame]]d for its [[baroque]] [[architecture]] and [[importance]] in [[musical]] [[history]].
#* '''1991''', {{w|Stephen Fry}}, ''The Liar'', p. 2:
#*: ''‘Take '''Salzburg'''. By no means the chief city of Austria, but a [[Jerusalem]] to any music lover...’''
# The [[present]] [[federal]] [[state]] of [[Austria]] [[surround]]ing the [[city]].
# {{lb|en|historical}} The [[former]] [[sovereign]] [[archbishopric]] [[surround]]ing the [[city]].

